observations.recommendation:
Require the Bids and Awards Committee and Office of the Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking documents enumerated in subsections (a) and (c), respectively, to establish the validity and propriety of the transactions;

Require the BAC to submit a written explanation of the deficiencies noted on the submitted documents; and

Collect liquidated damages for the cost of unperformed work for every day of delay from target completion date to actual completion of the project.

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to undertake the following courses of action:

To strictly require the submission of documentary requirements for future advance/ progress payments;

To accurately record the advance payment for mobilization and progress payments, ensuring proper recoupment of advance payments.

Refrain from incurring payments for meals and snacks for the conduct of the regular functions of the legislative body and bids and awards committee. If the meals and snacks are warranted, it shall be charged against their Representation Allowances;

Refrain from incurring payments for meals and snacks of personnel rendering regular duties or not included in official meetings.

Ensure that representation expenses incurred are duly supported by complete documentations to validate claims.

We recommended that the local government unit ensure proper management and accounting of its properties by observing the procedures provided by existing rules and regulations in the custody and management of properties specifically:
Keeping of Property Cards per category of Property, Plant and Equipment, and preparing and submitting RPCPPE or Physical Inventory Report by the General Services Officer, Supply Officer or the Local Treasurer, as the case maybe;
Maintaining/Updating Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards for each category of assets by the Municipal Accountant;
Implementation of the guidelines and procedures for the one-time cleansing of PPEs of the LGU per COA Circular 2020-006.
The Municipal Treasurers Office will comply with the recommendation. As of this date, we are gathering data from the different offices of the LGU to be submitted to Accounting Office for reconciliation. They are also preparing stickers for the detailed acquisition of such equipment. The staff will be reminded of the scheduled submission of the Physical Inventory Report.

We recommended that Management strictly comply with the accounting and reporting guidelines on the Local Roads Asset Management System prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015. We further recommend the following courses of action:

Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network, and disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the total road network system;

Require the Municipal Treasurer, in the absence of General Services Officer, to maintain a Report of the Local Road Network and Road Map, and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;

Create an inventory committee to conduct the physical count and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System.

In view of the foregoing, we recommended that Management –

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit the Sangguniang Bayan Ordinance and authorization/approval of Sangguniang Panlalawigan to support the budgetary realignment of savings from MOOE to Capital Outlay; 

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer, in coordination with the Bids and Awards Committee, to ensure to be more prudent in purchasing portable electronic devices which are essential and responsive to the exigency of the service, and see to it that procurement of electronic devices is within the bounds of propriety. Strict compliance with the guidelines on the prevention of unnecessary and extravagant expenditures as provided under COA Circular No. 2012-003 is further recommended.

In view of the foregoing, we recommended that Management –

Submit the Sangguniang Bayan Resolution approving any savings from the local budget and the documentary requirements prescribed under Section 5.7.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 to support the payment of honoraria under the General Fund;

Ensure that the honoraria of the BAC Chairman and members of Bids and Awards Committee (BAC), Technical Working Group and BAC Secretariat are charged only against the sources enumerated in Section 3.1, and that the provisions of Sections 3.3 and 3.5 of DBM Budget Circular No. 2007-3 dated November 29, 2007 should be strictly observed in the use of savings for payment of honoraria;

Ensure that all disbursements are duly supported with complete documentation in compliance with the provision of Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445.

We recommended that Management:

Require the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) and the BAC Secretariat to post all NOA, contract, or purchase order in the website of the local government unit, if any, or any conspicuous place in the premises of the PE and GPPB online portal for Emergency Procurement under the Bayanihan Act for information purposes and to require the submission of the mandatory documentary requirements from the concerned suppliers;

Require the Municipal Accountant, MDRRMO and MSWDO to submit the list of affected families and proof of receipt of distribution of relief goods and other supporting documents and to submit comments/justifications on the deficiencies noted.

